          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-eagle space-y-2 mb-4 ml-4">
            <li>Project is completed and approved by client according to agreed specifications</li>
            <li>Client fails to respond to communications or provide required materials within 30 days</li>
            <li>Changes in client preferences after approval of designs/deliverables</li>
            <li>Third-party costs have been incurred (domain registration, hosting, plugins, etc.)</li>
            <li>Client violates terms of service or engages in abusive behavior</li>
            <li>Refund request is made more than 14 days after final project delivery</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3 mt-6">Our Revision Process</h3>
          <p class="text-eagle leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Before requesting a refund, we encourage you to work with us through our revision process:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-eagle space-y-2 mb-4 ml-4">
            <li>All packages include multiple revision rounds at no extra cost</li>
            <li>Clear communication of concerns and desired changes</li>
            <li>Opportunity to address issues before project completion</li>
            <li>Good-faith collaboration to achieve your vision</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3 mt-6">Alternative Resolution</h3>
          <p class="text-eagle leading-relaxed mb-4">
            In cases where a full refund may not be applicable, we may offer:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-eagle space-y-2 mb-4 ml-4">
            <li>Store credit toward future services (125% of refund amount)</li>
            <li>Additional revision rounds to address concerns</li>
            <li>Partial refund based on work completed</li>
            <li>Service package upgrade or modification</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3 mt-6">How to Request a Refund</h3>
          <p class="text-eagle leading-relaxed mb-4">
            To request a refund, please email <a href="mailto:support@self-labs.io" class="text-orange underline">support@self-labs.io</a> 
            with your order number and detailed explanation. We'll review your request within 2 business days and work with you 
            to find a fair resolution. Approved refunds are processed within 5-10 business days.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3 mt-6">Money-Back Guarantee</h3>
          <p class="text-eagle leading-relaxed mb-4">
            <strong>First-Time Clients:</strong> If you're working with us for the first time and aren't satisfied 
            with our work after the first design milestone, we'll either revise until you're happy or provide a full 
            refundâno questions asked. Your satisfaction is our priority.
          </p>

          <p class="text-eagle leading-relaxed mt-6 text-sm italic">
            This refund policy applies to services purchased directly from Self Labs. For purchases made through 
            third-party platforms (including ChatGPT Instant Checkout), the platform's refund policies may also apply.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-orange mb-3">10. Modifications</h2>
          <p class="text-eagle leading-relaxed">
            We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Changes will be effective immediately upon 
            posting to our website. Your continued use of our services constitutes acceptance of any changes.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-orange mb-3">11. Intellectual Property Rights</h2>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">11.1 Client Content</h3>
          <p class="text-eagle leading-relaxed mb-4">
            You retain all rights to content, materials, and intellectual property you provide to us ("Client Content"). 
            You grant us a limited, non-exclusive license to use Client Content solely for the purpose of providing our services.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">11.2 Our Work Product</h3>
          <p class="text-eagle leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Upon full payment, you own the final deliverables including custom code, designs, and content created specifically 
            for your project. We retain rights to our proprietary tools, methodologies, and pre-existing intellectual property.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">11.3 Portfolio Rights</h3>
          <p class="text-eagle leading-relaxed">
            We retain the right to showcase completed work in our portfolio, case studies, and marketing materials unless 
            otherwise agreed in writing. We will not use confidential or proprietary client information in our marketing.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-orange mb-3">12. Project Management & Communication</h2>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">12.1 Project Scope</h3>
          <p class="text-eagle leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Project scope is defined in written proposals or agreements. Changes to scope may result in additional charges 
            and timeline adjustments. All scope changes must be approved in writing by both parties.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">12.2 Client Responsibilities</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-eagle space-y-2 ml-4 mb-4">
            <li>Provide accurate and complete information about your business and requirements</li>
            <li>Respond to requests for feedback and approvals within 5 business days</li>
            <li>Provide necessary content, images, and materials in agreed formats</li>
            <li>Ensure you have rights to all content and materials you provide</li>
            <li>Designate a single point of contact for project communication</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">12.3 Timeline Expectations</h3>
          <p class="text-eagle leading-relaxed">
            Project timelines are estimates based on client responsiveness and scope. Delays caused by client unavailability 
            or late feedback may extend project completion dates. We will communicate any timeline changes promptly.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-orange mb-3">13. Payment Terms & Billing</h2>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">13.1 Payment Processing</h3>
          <p class="text-eagle leading-relaxed mb-4">
            All payments are processed securely through Stripe. We accept major credit cards and digital payment methods. 
            Payment information is encrypted and processed according to PCI DSS standards.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">13.2 Payment Schedule</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-eagle space-y-2 ml-4 mb-4">
            <li><strong>One-Time Projects:</strong> 50% deposit required to begin work, balance due upon completion</li>
            <li><strong>Monthly Retainers:</strong> Billed in advance on the 1st of each month</li>
            <li><strong>Additional Work:</strong> Billed upon completion or as agreed in writing</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">13.3 Late Payments</h3>
          <p class="text-eagle leading-relaxed">
            Payments are due within 15 days of invoice date. Late payments may incur a 1.5% monthly service charge. 
            We reserve the right to suspend services for accounts with payments overdue by 30 days or more.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
